<concept id="concept_B32294CC9FA643A2A14A74B1DAA49C95" xml:lang="de-de">
    <title>Integrating Certificates for Trusted Communication</title>
    <conbody>
        <p>Certificates are required for <ph conref="../Product_Name.xml#ProductNameTopic/Product_Abbr"
                /> to authenticate a calling client and to allow for trusted communication between <ph
                conref="../Product_Name.xml#ProductNameTopic/Product_Abbr"
            /> and an application underlying a technical service.</p>
        <p>The following organizations are involved in handling certificates: </p>
        <ul>
            <li>Operator</li>
            <li>Technology providers integrating their applications with <ph
                    conref="../Product_Name.xml#ProductNameTopic/Product_Abbr"/></li>
            <li>Any other organization using Web service calls to or from <ph
                    conref="../Product_Name.xml#ProductNameTopic/Product_Abbr"/></li>
            <!--li>PSPs whose services are to be integrated with <ph
                    conref="../Product_Name.xml#ProductNameTopic/Product_Abbr"
                /> for billing, invoicing, and payment collection. </li-->
        </ul>
    </conbody>
</concept>
